{
  "texts": [
    "We consider this task to be a form of thematic coding.",
    "We refer to this type of data-driven, inductive task as open and falling on the opposite side of the spectrum into unsupervised territory as a result of the limited guidance provided to the model.",
    "This task takes advantage of LLM's ability to identify patterns while taking the meaning of words into account.",
    "We also discuss the importance of validating the model, the various robustness tests that can be used for validation, and other problems to be aware of when using LLMs.",
    "Both supervised and unsupervised approaches share some common elements, including data collection and cleaning; exploratory qualitative analysis of all or a portion of the data by the researchers; and interpretive analysis consisting of prompt development, performance of classification and coding tasks, and delivering analytical queries (see Figure 2)."
  ]
}